Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on using oblique light sheet microscopy for whole brain imaging and proposes a neural network-based approach for automated tracing of neuronal arbors. This involves image processing and analysis techniques commonly used in computer vision.
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for automated tracing of neuronal arbors, which falls under the scope of neural computing.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for automated tracing of neuronal arbors using neural networks.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach for automated tracing of neuronal arbors using neural networks.
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper also discusses a scalable, distributed implementation for reconstructing large datasets, which involves software engineering techniques.
